                <head>No. 237<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>By the end of 1953 agreement had been reached among the United States, the United
                    Kingdom, France, and the Soviet Union to hold a four-power conference in Berlin
                    to discuss, among other things, the future of Germany. The conference opened
                    January 25 in the Allied Control Authority building in West Berlin and met until
                    February 18 when it adjourned without results. For documentation on the
                    conference, see <ref target="#d257">Documents 257</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
